# 🚲 Cyclistic Bike-Share Case Study (Google Data Analytics Capstone)

## 📋 Project Overview
This repository contains the programming assets for my Cyclistic Bike-Share case study, completed as part of the Google Data Analytics Professional Certificate. The project analyzes historical trip data from a fictional bike-share company to identify behavioral differences between casual riders and annual members, driving data-informed marketing strategies for user conversion.

👉 **[View the Full Comprehensive Case Study & Narrative on Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/code/lukeshofestall/cyclistic-case-study-capstone)**

---

## 📂 Repository Contents
* **`cyclistic-case-study-capstone.ipynb`**: The complete Python Jupyter Notebook covering data cleaning, exploratory data analysis (EDA), and data visualizations using Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, and Seaborn.
* **`annual_summary.csv`**: Aggregated metric summaries capturing total ride counts and average trip durations by user type.
* **`day_of_the_week_usage.csv`**: Weekly behavioral trends isolating specific days when casual riders vs. annual members utilize the fleet.
* **`monthly_usage.csv`**: Seasonal variations tracking month-over-month volume shifts across the calendar year.
